of that?

13:44.191 --> 13:45.658
Yeah, I checked her fucking I.D.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.460
This fucking bartender.

13:47.594 --> 13:49.129
You're telling me she's 21?

13:49.262 --> 13:51.831
What I'm telling you
is that her I.D. says she's 21,

13:51.999 --> 13:54.902
just like most of your crew have
valid Social Security numbers.

13:55.002 --> 13:56.970
- Touché.
- [chuckles]

13:57.104 --> 13:58.005
Do you want another?

13:58.171 --> 13:59.439
Yeah, I might as well.

14:02.976 --> 14:05.845
Girl's right. You're an asshole.

14:06.013 --> 14:07.948
Maybe she doesn't have
any other choice.

14:08.081 --> 14:09.849
Are you shitting me?

14:10.017 --> 14:11.651
Look around this place.
You see all these waitresses

14:11.784 --> 14:15.022
working their asses off
for a third of what she makes?

14:15.188 --> 14:17.657
No, she had a choice
and she chose the shortcut,

14:17.790 --> 14:19.692
which is always
the longest road.

14:21.661 --> 14:23.096
Boomtowns.

14:24.464 --> 14:26.934
Hell, we're not any different
than Tombstone

14:27.034 --> 14:31.038
or Dodge City or San Francisco.

14:31.204 --> 14:33.806
First comes the dreamers,
then the bankers,

14:33.941 --> 14:36.309
then the salesmen,
then the sharks,

14:36.443 --> 14:39.079
then the desperate,
and then the thieves.

14:41.048 --> 14:43.016
What happens in a bust?

14:47.420 --> 14:52.292
Well, you want oil to live
above 60 but below 90.

14:52.392 --> 14:53.460
And don't get me wrong,

14:53.593 --> 14:56.329
we're still printing money
at 90, but...

14:56.463 --> 14:59.399
gas gets up over $3.50
a gallon, it starts to pinch.

14:59.566 --> 15:02.202
It hits a hundred,
every product in America

15:02.369 --> 15:03.870
has to readjust its price.

15:04.037 --> 15:06.974
$78 a barrel,
that's about perfect.

15:07.107 --> 15:08.808
You know, brings enough profit
to keep exploring,

15:08.942 --> 15:11.678
but it don't sting as much
at the pump.

15:11.811 --> 15:13.546
Unless, of course,
you're in California.

15:13.713 --> 15:16.316
I mean, they tax the shit
out of it out there.

15:16.449 --> 15:20.320
It could be $45 a barrel, and
it's still four dollars to pump.

15:20.420 --> 15:22.755
I don't know how those
son-bitches do it out there.

15:23.890 --> 15:26.926
2020, a barrel of oil
was worthless.

15:27.060 --> 15:29.896
This place became a ghost town.

15:30.030 --> 15:31.764
And nobody's immune.

15:32.832 --> 15:35.202
Kids have to quit college.

15:35.335 --> 15:38.271
Trucks get sold or repo'd.

15:38.405 --> 15:39.772
Houses, too.

15:39.906 --> 15:41.008
People quit going to the doctor

15:41.141 --> 15:43.410
'cause they lost
their insurance.

15:44.477 --> 15:47.580
Yeah, a bust affects
everything in a town like this.

15:47.714 --> 15:49.582
Even the lifespan
of the population.

15:49.749 --> 15:52.085
The smart ones,
they pay cash for everything

15:52.252 --> 15:55.522
and then sock away enough
to ride out the troughs,

15:55.655 --> 15:58.158
but there ain't
that many smart ones.

15:59.692 --> 16:02.062
This is how you have
a celebration drink?

16:02.195 --> 16:03.830
Well, shit, you asked.

16:06.799 --> 16:09.569
<i>♪ Well, if you've been true ♪</i>

16:09.702 --> 16:11.104
<i>♪ Well,
if you've been true ♪</i>

16:22.449 --> 16:25.285
- [club manager] Mrs. Norris.
- Oh, I'm Mrs. Russo now.

16:25.418 --> 16:26.719
Ah, yes.

16:26.819 --> 16:28.921
The club is closed for
a private event this evening.

16:29.056 --> 16:30.257
Really?

16:30.390 --> 16:32.325
- Yes, ma'am.
- What's the event?

16:33.426 --> 16:34.461
The private kind.

16:34.627 --> 16:36.029
Mm-hmm.

16:37.797 --> 16:41.000
[whistles]
Let's go.

16:41.834 --> 16:43.270
Where are we going now?

16:43.403 --> 16:46.005
Who cares? Not here.

16:46.139 --> 16:47.874
<i>♪ hopeful music ♪</i>

16:48.141 --> 16:51.010
<i>***</i>

17:18.705 --> 17:20.873
<i>***</i>

17:50.370 --> 17:52.239
<i>***</i>

18:17.897 --> 18:20.300
<i>***</i>

18:46.859 --> 18:49.329
<i>♪ "Wrecked"
by Turnpike Troubadours ♪</i>

18:49.596 --> 18:50.963
<i>***</i>

18:51.097 --> 18:53.900
[indistinct chatter]

18:59.739 --> 19:02.275
<i>♪ Well, lookin' back
when I met you... ♪</i>

19:02.409 --> 19:04.444
[man] <i>When I first went
to work in the oil field,</i>

19:04.577 --> 19:06.078
<i>there were three
kinds of people:</i>

19:06.213 --> 19:09.549
worms, ginsels and skinheads.

19:09.682 --> 19:12.485
[Tommy] So, Monty got in
at $900 an acre

19:12.619 --> 19:15.054
- on a 30,000-acre track in 2011.
- [Rebecca] Mm-hmm.

19:15.188 --> 19:17.224
Started fracking
and drilling horizontals.

19:17.324 --> 19:19.125
This whole area was played out.

19:19.292 --> 19:21.728
They'd been drilling here
since 1921.

19:21.828 --> 19:23.062
Pretty worn.

19:23.196 --> 19:25.097
Well, Monty's got a lease
outside Midland

19:25.232 --> 19:28.301
in an area they call
the Delaware Subbasin.

19:28.435 --> 19:31.638
He sold 10,000 acres in 2019

19:31.804 --> 19:33.573
for $70,000 an acre.

19:33.706 --> 19:36.609
$700 million dollars
in one transaction.

19:36.743 --> 19:39.979
And then, in 2020,
he bought it all back

19:40.112 --> 19:41.914
at ten cents on the dollar.

19:42.048 --> 19:44.751
- [chuckles]
- [scoffs] Wow.

19:44.851 --> 19:47.654
Paid 'em with their own money.
And he grew up with nothing.

19:47.820 --> 19:49.789
Raised in a little trailer park
in Pennsylvania.

19:49.922 --> 19:52.158
He got a scholarship
to play ball at Tech.

19:52.325 --> 19:53.626
He was smart enough
to know football

19:53.760 --> 19:56.195
wasn't really a business,
it was more of a dream, so...

19:56.363 --> 19:57.930
[Rebecca]
I thought you said it's dreamers

19:58.030 --> 19:59.532
who come to this place.

19:59.699 --> 20:00.667
Well, it can be the dream,

20:00.800 --> 20:01.934
but you got to have a plan,
you know?

20:02.034 --> 20:03.270
Most don't.

20:03.403 --> 20:05.137
Monty always had a plan.

20:05.272 --> 20:06.406
Matter of fact,
I think he made more money

20:06.506 --> 20:09.008
during the busts
than he did the booms.

20:09.876 --> 20:11.110
Evening, ladies.

20:11.210 --> 20:12.712
- Evening.
- Breakfast or supper?

20:12.879 --> 20:14.314
Happy hour.

20:14.447 --> 20:15.782
- All right, my kind of table.
- [chuckles]

20:15.882 --> 20:17.350
Two Tito's margaritas.

20:17.484 --> 20:18.785
Tito's is a vodka.

20:18.885 --> 20:20.320
I'm trying to behave.

20:20.453 --> 20:21.554
[chuckles]
Gotcha.

20:21.688 --> 20:23.723
Y'all want some appetizers
for the table?

20:23.890 --> 20:25.057
Do you have anything keto?

20:25.191 --> 20:27.360
Uh, shrimp cocktail
is pretty keto.

20:27.494 --> 20:30.397
Hmm. Little far
from the ocean for seafood.

20:30.530 --> 20:31.531
Well, we can fry 'em.

20:31.698 --> 20:33.633
Kind of defeats the purpose,
don't you think?

20:33.766 --> 20:36.936
You know, they grind up
them shrimp tails

20:37.036 --> 20:39.005
and they put 'em
in all those weight-loss pills,

20:39.138 --> 20:41.808
so feet for tail,
you ain't gaining a pound.

20:41.908 --> 20:42.975
Is that true?

20:43.075 --> 20:44.944
Proof is in the pudding, darling.

20:45.044 --> 20:47.547
Hmm?
[chuckles]

20:47.680 --> 20:49.081
We'll do a basket of the shrimp.

20:49.248 --> 20:50.417
You got it.

20:51.384 --> 20:53.786
You learn something new
every day.

20:58.525 --> 21:00.493
That looks like Daddy.

21:03.095 --> 21:05.732
That sorry son of a bitch.

21:08.167 --> 21:10.069
[Tommy]
You want another drink?

21:10.236 --> 21:12.772
No, I got to drive,
and so do you.

21:12.905 --> 21:14.641
There ain't no alcohol in this.

21:15.742 --> 21:17.510
Those are nonalcoholic?

21:17.644 --> 21:19.846
Yeah, they're nonalcoholic
if you're an alcoholic.

21:19.979 --> 21:22.248
[Tommy] I swear to God,
Barney is a trust-fund kid

21:22.382 --> 21:23.650
that bartends for fun,

21:23.750 --> 21:25.318
'cause he damn sure
don't want a tip.

21:25.418 --> 21:27.920
No, I divorced whiskey
about nine years ago.

21:28.087 --> 21:29.589
Remember us, motherfucker?

21:29.756 --> 21:31.958
Matter of fact,
the same week I divorced her.

21:32.124 --> 21:33.326
You got a side piece?

21:33.426 --> 21:35.294
Daddy, you don't have
another daughter, do you?

21:35.462 --> 21:38.731
First off, goddamn, girls.

21:38.865 --> 21:40.199
No, honey,
you're my only daughter.

21:40.333 --> 21:42.101
And by the way, you have to have

21:42.268 --> 21:44.170
a main piece before
you can have a side piece,

21:44.270 --> 21:45.538
and I ain't got either one.

21:45.638 --> 21:47.540
This is Rebecca "Falcon."

21:47.674 --> 21:49.542
She's an attorney
representing the company.

21:49.676 --> 21:52.144
Sounds like a fucking
Marvel character.

21:52.278 --> 21:55.748
It's pronounced "Fal-coney,"
and it sounds like it's Italian.

21:55.882 --> 21:57.917
- Mm-hmm.
- We just got out of court.

21:58.050 --> 22:00.086
Well, it looks
like it went well.

22:00.219 --> 22:01.754
Why are you here?

22:01.888 --> 22:03.490
[Angela]
We wanted a drink.

22:03.656 --> 22:05.425
She's on spring break,

22:05.558 --> 22:07.794
and she should be drinking.
Come on.

22:07.960 --> 22:09.295
This is Aledo's
mother of the year,

22:09.429 --> 22:10.497
in case you were wondering.

22:10.663 --> 22:12.799
- [Angela] Thank you.
- Well, y'all enjoy it

22:12.932 --> 22:13.700
'cause we're about to head out.

22:13.800 --> 22:15.334
Together?

22:16.469 --> 22:18.638
Well...
[sighs]

22:18.805 --> 22:20.139
as a matter of coincidence,

22:20.306 --> 22:22.308
we will be leaving the café
at the same time,

22:22.475 --> 22:24.276
and we're gonna get
in different cars

22:24.411 --> 22:25.745
and go to our respective homes.

22:25.878 --> 22:28.114
Not that I owe you
a fucking explanation.

22:28.247 --> 22:29.982
Well, you don't want
to stay for supper?

22:30.116 --> 22:32.652
- No, honey.
- [Angela] Yeah, Tommy.

22:32.785 --> 22:33.986
Stay for supper.

22:34.721 --> 22:37.323
Your lawyer and her lips
are welcome to join us.

22:37.457 --> 22:38.357
No, I'm sure
she'd rather go home

22:38.525 --> 22:39.992
and push her cuticles back

22:40.126 --> 22:41.661
with a fucking screwdriver.

22:41.794 --> 22:43.029
I'd love to join.

22:44.196 --> 22:47.667
Well... suit yourself.

22:47.800 --> 22:49.569
We have a table right there.

22:51.438 --> 22:52.939
Now, you know
this has the potential

22:53.039 --> 22:54.006
of becoming a real scene,

22:54.140 --> 22:55.274
- you understand that, right?
- Mm-hmm.

22:55.408 --> 22:56.509
I have a funny feeling

22:56.676 --> 22:58.778
I'm gonna learn a lot
about you tonight, Tommy.

22:58.878 --> 23:00.146
Let me get this.

23:00.279 --> 23:01.614
I already got it.

23:01.714 --> 23:05.351
<i>♪ Caught up in your headlights ♪</i>

23:05.518 --> 23:09.021
<i>♪ Well, I was blindsided
in plain sight ♪</i>

23:09.188 --> 23:11.424
[machinery whirring]

23:17.196 --> 23:19.231
<i>♪ purposeful music ♪</i>

23:19.566 --> 23:21.434
<i>***</i>

23:44.256 --> 23:46.759
Oh, stop, stop!
[shouting]

23:46.926 --> 23:50.129
- [Boss] What's going on?
- [screaming]

23:50.262 --> 23:51.498
[Manuel]
Stop work, fucking stop!

23:51.598 --> 23:53.633
The fuck is going on, Antonio?

23:53.766 --> 23:56.903
[screaming]

23:57.036 --> 23:59.271
- Kill the rig!
- Oh, shit, he hurt.

23:59.438 --> 24:01.140
- Fuck. Fuck, fuck.
- Now go get him, go get him.

24:01.273 --> 24:02.575
He coming.

24:05.077 --> 24:06.178
Ah, hurry up!

24:06.278 --> 24:08.948
[groaning]

24:11.684 --> 24:12.919
Get on the blocks, worm.

24:13.052 --> 24:13.986
What?

24:14.153 --> 24:15.655
Get on the blocks, worm.

24:16.523 --> 24:18.124
Hold on tight.

24:20.560 --> 24:22.529
[Manuel]
Antonio, we're coming.

24:24.063 --> 24:25.331
[groaning]

24:25.498 --> 24:26.866
[Boss]
Shit.

24:26.966 --> 24:28.067
You okay?

24:28.200 --> 24:29.602
[Manuel speaks Spanish]

24:29.736 --> 24:31.337
[Antonio screaming]

24:33.205 --> 24:34.273
Now I got to unclip him.

24:34.406 --> 24:35.207
Oh, fuck.

24:35.307 --> 24:36.743
[Antonio screams]

24:36.876 --> 24:38.110
Lean back, lean back, lean back!

24:38.244 --> 24:39.879
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

24:39.979 --> 24:41.514
All right, all right, all right.
Give him to me.

24:42.715 --> 24:44.984
- I got him, I got him.
- He's passing out!

24:45.151 --> 24:46.753
- Hold on, hold on.
- [Boss] Take him down slow!

24:46.853 --> 24:47.987
All right, let's go down!

24:51.691 --> 24:53.726
I got him, I got him.

24:58.965 --> 25:00.933
Oh, shit!

25:02.101 --> 25:04.203
Fuck!

25:04.370 --> 25:05.872
[engine starts]

25:11.644 --> 25:13.179
[grunts]

25:13.345 --> 25:14.380
[Cooper]
He's out, he's out!

25:14.547 --> 25:15.548
[Boss]
I got him, I got him!

25:15.682 --> 25:17.116
[Cooper]
You got him?

25:17.216 --> 25:18.951
[Dale]
What the fuck happened?

25:19.085 --> 25:21.487
- Come right here. Come on now.
- Oh, shit, his hand's fucked.

25:21.621 --> 25:22.689
- Come on.
- Watch his head.

25:22.822 --> 25:24.591
Yeah, watch his head.
Manny, you got him?

25:24.691 --> 25:26.025
- Boss, get down here!
- [Boss] Yeah!

25:26.158 --> 25:27.359
Cooper,
get that front door open!

25:27.526 --> 25:28.494
[Manuel shouts indistinctly]

25:28.628 --> 25:30.296
- [Boss] I'm coming.
- [grunting]

25:30.429 --> 25:31.530
I got him.

25:31.664 --> 25:33.299
- Go, go, go, go.
- [Dale] Goddamn it!

25:33.432 --> 25:34.701
[Manuel]
God... Shit.

25:34.834 --> 25:35.868
Keep that door open.

25:36.035 --> 25:37.003
Come on, get him in.

25:37.136 --> 25:38.270
Push.

25:38.370 --> 25:39.305
[Dale]
We'll get him in.

25:39.405 --> 25:40.707
You're all right, Tony.

25:40.840 --> 25:42.508
- [Boss] Yeah, pull.
- You're all right, Tony.

25:42.642 --> 25:44.343
[Boss]
He's in.

25:44.476 --> 25:45.578
- [Dale] Boss!
- Yeah.

25:45.745 --> 25:47.346
You get that rig running!

25:47.914 --> 25:49.381
We need this well on line
in the morning!

25:49.515 --> 25:50.850
Yes, sir.

25:50.983 --> 25:51.884
We're a man down!

25:52.051 --> 25:53.419
That sounds
like a problem, Manny.

25:53.552 --> 25:54.754
I didn't ask you for a problem.

25:54.887 --> 25:57.624
I asked you for a solution.
Find one!

25:59.258 --> 26:01.060
[Dale]
Fuck.

26:08.567 --> 26:10.603
- Oh, fuck.
- [Manuel] Fuck.

26:12.538 --> 26:14.340
You know what
a derrickhand does, right?

26:14.440 --> 26:15.374
Yeah, f-feeds the pipe.

26:15.507 --> 26:17.810
Put this shit on.

26:19.411 --> 26:21.881
Feeds the pipe
into the fingers of the derrick.

26:22.014 --> 26:24.283
Just don't jam me the fuck up
down here, you got it?

26:25.351 --> 26:27.419
- I got it.
- Okay.

26:38.865 --> 26:42.334
[Angela] <i>My dream was
to see George Strait in concert.</i>

26:42.434 --> 26:43.770
That was part of the dream.

26:43.903 --> 26:45.738
The other part was
climbing him like a cat

26:45.872 --> 26:47.139
and riding that fine
son of a bitch

26:47.273 --> 26:48.775
until he had calluses
on his thighs.

26:48.908 --> 26:51.878
[chuckles]
So, it's my birthday,

26:51.978 --> 26:54.113
and we are flying high.

26:54.280 --> 26:55.547
Oil's over a hundred a barrel.

26:55.682 --> 26:57.016
- Hundred and forty-three.
- [Angela] Mm-hmm.

26:57.116 --> 27:00.519
So Tommy says,
"I'm gonna take you to Cancún.

27:00.619 --> 27:02.121
Grandparents are gonna
watch the kids."

27:02.254 --> 27:03.355
You were two, I think.

27:03.455 --> 27:05.825
Baby, you were just
like a fat, little bug.

27:05.958 --> 27:07.226
So we go to the FBO,

27:07.359 --> 27:10.629
get on this plane,
and I'm dressed for the beach.

27:10.763 --> 27:13.332
Plane takes off,
and not 20 minutes later

27:13.499 --> 27:14.834
we're landing.

27:15.001 --> 27:17.103
I look out the window,

27:17.236 --> 27:18.671
we're in Lubbock.

27:18.805 --> 27:20.807
Tommy says, "There's
some issue with the plane.

27:20.973 --> 27:22.975
Let's get something to eat."

27:23.109 --> 27:25.144
So we go to the Overton Hotel,

27:25.277 --> 27:27.246
and he says he's got a room.

27:27.379 --> 27:29.081
Now, I think he's being frisky

27:29.215 --> 27:32.484
'cause Tommy's still not above
making a detour for a good poke.

27:32.618 --> 27:33.652
Come on, honey,
don't say that...

27:33.786 --> 27:35.487
- Dad.
- ...in front of people. God.

27:35.621 --> 27:37.656
[laughter]

27:37.790 --> 27:40.659
[Angela]
We go out to this giant suite

27:40.827 --> 27:43.796
where there is
a black sequin ball gown

27:43.930 --> 27:44.964
laying on the bed.

27:45.097 --> 27:47.800
- Mm.
- And he says, "Put it on."

27:47.934 --> 27:49.535
I do.

27:49.668 --> 27:51.270
He comes out of the other room

27:51.370 --> 27:53.172
wearing this tux.

27:53.305 --> 27:56.375
And he says to me,

27:56.542 --> 27:59.378
"I lied to you, baby.

27:59.545 --> 28:01.380
We're not going to Mexico.

28:01.513 --> 28:03.950
We're gonna stay
right here in Lubbock,

28:04.050 --> 28:06.853
and I'm gonna make one half
of your dream come true."

28:06.986 --> 28:09.856
He takes me down to the ballroom

28:09.989 --> 28:13.726
where George Strait is
playing a private event.

28:14.794 --> 28:17.296
And we two-stepped
that dance floor

28:17.429 --> 28:20.199
with George Strait playing
just for us.

28:21.433 --> 28:23.402
<i>[Turnpike Troubadours'
"Empty as a Drum" playing]</i>

28:23.535 --> 28:26.505
<i>♪ And I'm gonna give it
one more minute... ♪</i>

28:26.638 --> 28:27.874
Three weeks later,

28:28.007 --> 28:30.676
the markets crashed
and oil dropped to 30.

28:30.810 --> 28:33.145
<i>♪ Empty as a drum... ♪</i>

28:33.279 --> 28:35.081
We lost everything.

28:35.214 --> 28:37.049
<i>♪ Could you spare a cigarette? ♪</i>

28:37.216 --> 28:40.152
<i>♪ I hate to be a bum... ♪</i>

28:41.253 --> 28:43.389
And I do mean everything.

28:45.992 --> 28:47.960
Shit, I just remembered,
I got to go.

28:49.061 --> 28:50.296
Can we get a ride back with you?

28:50.396 --> 28:51.764
Well, it's gonna be a while yet.

28:51.898 --> 28:55.001
I, uh, got to check
on a rig, so...

28:55.134 --> 28:57.569
- Oh, I can call an Uber.
- I can give you a ride.

28:58.670 --> 29:00.907
Well, I-I'll see you
at the house, hon.

29:01.040 --> 29:02.508
All right.

29:03.575 --> 29:04.944
<i>♪ When you darkened up... ♪</i>

29:05.111 --> 29:07.814
He doesn't like to talk
about the bust.

29:08.915 --> 29:12.018
No, I guess...
I guess he wouldn't.

29:14.020 --> 29:15.421
<i>♪ And you kissed me ♪</i>

29:16.488 --> 29:19.025
<i>♪ Said I can't say
that I'm great ♪</i>

29:19.158 --> 29:20.526
<i>♪ Oh, Lord, I hate it
that I'm... ♪</i>

29:20.659 --> 29:23.595
[machinery whirring]

29:44.917 --> 29:46.853
[whirring continues]

29:56.628 --> 29:58.497
- Tommy.
- Hey.

30:03.069 --> 30:05.437
You just got one floor hand.

30:05.571 --> 30:07.506
I had to send one
up the derrick.

30:07.639 --> 30:08.875
Derrickhand got smashed.

30:08.975 --> 30:10.576
Dale took him to the hospital.

30:10.676 --> 30:12.811
Is he gonna be all right?

30:12.979 --> 30:14.413
As long as he can jack off
with his left hand,

30:14.546 --> 30:16.415
I guess, yeah.

30:20.752 --> 30:22.654
Who is that?

30:23.522 --> 30:25.024
Not my idea.

30:31.497 --> 30:32.664
Manuel.

30:33.565 --> 30:35.034
Is it going smooth?

30:36.535 --> 30:38.037
Going smooth now.

31:17.176 --> 31:20.779
<i>♪ Yeah, it all went down
round these four walls ♪</i>

31:20.879 --> 31:22.581
<i>♪ If it's anyone's fault ♪</i>

31:22.714 --> 31:24.583
<i>♪ It's the lime and the salt ♪</i>

31:24.716 --> 31:26.418
<i>♪ For breaking
this broken heart ♪</i>

31:26.585 --> 31:28.387
<i>♪ I blame the bar... ♪</i>

31:28.554 --> 31:30.422
Remarried?

31:36.095 --> 31:37.663
What's your husband do?

31:37.796 --> 31:39.932
Builds hotels.

31:40.099 --> 31:42.101
<i>♪ That it didn't work out... ♪</i>

31:42.268 --> 31:44.836
Can I ask...

31:44.937 --> 31:46.772
what you're doing here?

31:46.905 --> 31:48.440
<i>♪ Being young and dumb... ♪</i>

31:48.607 --> 31:50.642
We're on spring break.

31:52.378 --> 31:54.180
You're not his type.

31:54.280 --> 31:57.249
You mean aside from
the 30-year age difference?

31:57.383 --> 32:01.187
Tommy needs calamities.
You know, he needs blowouts.

32:01.287 --> 32:03.622
He needs to control things
that can't be controlled

32:03.755 --> 32:05.824
to feel like a man.

32:05.924 --> 32:08.394
Why are you so jealous of me?

32:08.527 --> 32:09.761
Honey, I could sleep
with your boyfriend

32:09.928 --> 32:11.597
in front of you,
and there's nothing

32:11.730 --> 32:13.165
that you could do about it.

32:13.265 --> 32:15.968
I mean, why are you
jealous at all?

32:16.802 --> 32:18.737
He's not your husband.

32:19.738 --> 32:23.309
You have a different husband.

32:23.475 --> 32:24.643
[Angela scoffs]

32:24.776 --> 32:27.279
Fucking lawyers.

32:27.446 --> 32:31.883
<i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>

32:44.330 --> 32:46.298
[indistinct chatter on TV]

32:49.101 --> 32:51.103
Burning the midnight oil, Nate?

32:52.204 --> 32:53.172
One down, two to go.

32:56.475 --> 32:59.511
Working out settlements
for the Medina family.

32:59.645 --> 33:01.013
Did they file suit?

33:01.847 --> 33:03.482
Just getting ahead of it.

33:03.615 --> 33:04.650
Do the right thing.

33:04.816 --> 33:07.219
Well, those are two
different things, Nathan.

33:14.693 --> 33:16.628
You still awake, babe?

33:20.832 --> 33:22.401
[sighs]

33:22.501 --> 33:25.404
[woman on TV] <i>It's-it's crazy
'cause I-I believe you,</i>

33:25.504 --> 33:27.606
<i>but then I-I kind of don't,
you know?</i>

33:27.739 --> 33:29.175
[mutes audio]

33:29.308 --> 33:30.476
[sets remote down]

33:30.609 --> 33:32.444
Okay, what's wrong?

33:32.544 --> 33:35.381
She's a quitter.

33:35.514 --> 33:36.982
She's a fucking quitter.

33:37.116 --> 33:40.119
[sniffles] Market crashes
and she leaves you.

33:40.252 --> 33:42.020
Finds the richest man
who will have her.

33:42.154 --> 33:45.191
Well, honey,
there's more to it than that.

33:46.992 --> 33:48.527
No, there isn't.

33:51.463 --> 33:55.101
It's hard to describe what
it means to lose everything.

33:55.934 --> 33:57.869
Your house and your car.

33:58.003 --> 34:00.939
We had to sell
all of her jewelry.

34:01.039 --> 34:03.041
And I was no picnic.

34:03.209 --> 34:06.245
I hid in a bottle and didn't
come out till she left me.

34:07.379 --> 34:08.747
She was just trying to do
the best thing

34:08.914 --> 34:10.582
for you and your brother.

34:11.583 --> 34:14.420
And it's not worth
one tear out of you, hon.

34:14.586 --> 34:16.255
Okay.

34:17.156 --> 34:19.958
And it doesn't matter because...

34:20.058 --> 34:21.593
even if there
hadn't been a bust,

34:21.760 --> 34:23.295
we would've still ended.

34:24.563 --> 34:27.833
We're just oil and water.
You know what I mean?

34:27.966 --> 34:30.402
[both chuckle]

34:30.569 --> 34:31.870
[sniffles]

34:32.003 --> 34:33.805
You get some sleep, honey.

34:38.377 --> 34:40.346
I'll never quit you.

34:40.446 --> 34:42.414
No matter what the market does.

34:42.548 --> 34:45.517
I know you won't, baby girl.

34:47.919 --> 34:50.589
<i>♪ somber music ♪</i>

34:50.922 --> 34:52.791
<i>***</i>

34:54.593 --> 34:56.562
[Angela crying]

35:02.568 --> 35:04.136
[sobbing]

35:05.737 --> 35:08.340
Every damn woman in my life.

35:19.551 --> 35:20.952
All right, let me have it.

35:22.788 --> 35:25.157
We were great together,
weren't we?

35:26.392 --> 35:27.793
Honey... [chuckles]

35:27.926 --> 35:30.262
We had a terrible marriage,

35:30.396 --> 35:33.965
interrupted
by brief moments of joy.

35:34.099 --> 35:36.668
I mean, remember,
you were pretty miserable

35:36.802 --> 35:38.370
during the booms, don't forget.

35:40.172 --> 35:41.773
You were always gone.

35:41.907 --> 35:44.075
And I'll always be gone.
That's the job, hon.

35:44.210 --> 35:46.212
I mean, we had great sex

35:46.312 --> 35:48.547
and I made you laugh,
that was it.

35:50.081 --> 35:51.717
I've lived the alternative.

35:51.817 --> 35:53.252
[sighs]

35:53.352 --> 35:56.355
I'll take great sex
and a laugh any day.

35:57.923 --> 35:59.258
What else is there?

35:59.358 --> 36:01.827
Look, I don't have a side piece

36:01.993 --> 36:04.663
and I'm not looking
to be one myself.

36:11.670 --> 36:13.171
I'm gonna leave him.

36:17.142 --> 36:18.810
That's a pretty nice house
he's got.

36:18.944 --> 36:20.379
[chuckles]

36:20.546 --> 36:23.549
It's a five-minute walk
to the fucking kitchen.

36:23.715 --> 36:25.083
Big, nice jet.

36:25.917 --> 36:29.788
The jet is nice, but...

36:29.888 --> 36:33.792
successful relationships
require a sacrifice.

36:33.925 --> 36:36.295
It's gonna be hard
to give up that Bentley.

36:37.296 --> 36:39.331
The Bentley's in my name, baby.

36:39.465 --> 36:41.733
This ain't my first rodeo.

36:41.867 --> 36:42.834
[chuckles]

36:42.968 --> 36:44.736
Say yes.

36:44.870 --> 36:46.372
It's a huge mistake.

36:46.538 --> 36:48.073
Say yes.

36:49.040 --> 36:50.576
I got three roommates.

36:50.742 --> 36:52.077
Say yes.

36:52.711 --> 36:54.446
[grunts]

36:56.715 --> 36:58.884
Oh, fuck.

36:59.017 --> 37:01.287
That's the plan, baby.

37:17.569 --> 37:18.437
That's a lot of homework.

37:18.604 --> 37:19.738
[both yelp]

37:19.905 --> 37:21.340
What are you doing?

37:21.473 --> 37:23.442
Working. What the fuck?

37:23.575 --> 37:24.543
[footfalls approach]

37:24.676 --> 37:27.112
Nate, that's your
last cup of coffee.

37:27.279 --> 37:29.448
Honey, please put
some clothes on.

37:29.615 --> 37:30.582
Somebody's gonna have
a heart attack.

37:30.749 --> 37:32.451
Well, I need
to go shopping, then.

37:32.618 --> 37:35.153
The only clothes I have
were to seduce my boyfriend.

37:36.254 --> 37:37.188
Don't have that problem anymore.

37:37.323 --> 37:38.490
You certainly do not.

37:39.591 --> 37:42.428
- Busy kitchen.
- Yeah.

37:43.829 --> 37:45.597
I'm going to my room.

37:45.731 --> 37:48.300
Discretion's the better part
of valor, Nate.

37:48.467 --> 37:49.401
[Nathan sighs]

37:50.602 --> 37:52.103
[Nathan]
Oh, God.

37:55.874 --> 37:57.108
[door opens]

37:57.242 --> 37:58.477
[coffee pouring]

37:58.644 --> 37:59.745
[door closes]

37:59.878 --> 38:01.146
What?

38:02.113 --> 38:03.715
[squeals]

38:03.849 --> 38:06.385
[laughter]

38:07.619 --> 38:09.821
All right, we're gonna have
a little fucked-up family hug?

38:09.988 --> 38:11.623
[Angela squeals]

38:11.757 --> 38:13.459
[laughter]

38:13.592 --> 38:14.960
Are we moving here for good?

38:15.093 --> 38:16.662
Moving here for good, honey.

38:16.795 --> 38:18.330
[contented sigh]

38:18.497 --> 38:19.798
Wow.

38:19.931 --> 38:22.668
Wow, you must've really
pulled out the special sauce.

38:22.834 --> 38:25.203
Daddy told me just last night
how bad y'all are together.

38:25.303 --> 38:26.972
Really?

38:27.138 --> 38:28.273
[fridge door opens]

38:28.407 --> 38:30.208
Well, she was taking that
out of context.

38:30.308 --> 38:31.176
Mm-hmm.

38:31.309 --> 38:32.177
Anyway, I got a big day,

38:32.310 --> 38:33.379
so I'm gonna get out of here.

38:34.780 --> 38:35.614
Bye, honey.

38:35.747 --> 38:38.016
- Hey.
- Yeah?

38:45.256 --> 38:46.925
- Ow. Goddamn.
- [laughs]

38:47.058 --> 38:48.894
See you later.

38:48.994 --> 38:50.396
[Tommy]
Ah, yeah.

38:51.430 --> 38:53.999
I must be
out of my fucking mind.

38:54.132 --> 38:56.668
<i>♪ optimistic music ♪</i>

38:57.002 --> 38:59.371
<i>***</i>

39:02.240 --> 39:05.276
[machinery creaking]

39:27.733 --> 39:29.601
<i>***</i>

39:41.079 --> 39:43.014
- Dale.
- Yeah.

39:43.148 --> 39:45.684
- What's it read?
- Well, we just got it going.

39:45.817 --> 39:47.553
And, uh...

39:49.154 --> 39:50.856
Oh. Here we go.

39:50.989 --> 39:53.492
- We got a fucking gusher, boys.
- Yeah, we do.

39:57.095 --> 39:59.831
[phone rings]

39:59.931 --> 40:01.099
Hey, how'd it go?

40:01.266 --> 40:02.568
She's running.

40:02.701 --> 40:03.502
<i>Good.</i>

40:03.635 --> 40:04.903
Can you give me some numbers?

40:05.036 --> 40:08.406
She'll pump over 250 a day.
We're in a good pocket.

40:08.574 --> 40:11.677
Well, I don't like gambling,
but it paid off this time.

40:11.777 --> 40:13.912
- Good work.
<i>- Thank you, sir.</i>

40:17.115 --> 40:19.150
<i>♪ tranquil music ♪</i>

40:19.417 --> 40:21.620
<i>***</i>

40:29.695 --> 40:30.696
How'd he do?

40:30.796 --> 40:32.798
Stepped up
when we needed him most.

40:32.931 --> 40:35.266
Stepped up big-time.

40:35.433 --> 40:36.568
That boy worked the derrick

40:36.702 --> 40:38.036
like he'd been doing it
all winter.

40:38.169 --> 40:39.671
All right.

40:47.112 --> 40:48.313
Well...

40:53.084 --> 40:54.620
I want you to come
see your mama.

40:54.753 --> 40:56.287
She's still here?

40:56.421 --> 40:57.355
She's gonna stick around
a while.

40:57.455 --> 40:59.090
We're gonna give it
another shot.

40:59.224 --> 41:00.992
Why would you do that?

41:01.126 --> 41:04.129
'Cause that's how
fucking stupid I am.

41:06.798 --> 41:08.366
[chuckles softly]

41:22.180 --> 41:25.050
<i>***</i>

41:47.873 --> 41:49.808
[phone buzzing]

41:55.113 --> 41:56.114
Yeah.

41:56.247 --> 41:57.683
[Ariana clears throat]
<i>Cooper.</i>

41:57.816 --> 41:59.785
Yeah, who's this?

42:00.986 --> 42:02.053
<i>Ariana.</i>

42:05.891 --> 42:07.258
How are you?

42:07.358 --> 42:10.461
<i>Um... been better.</i>

42:10.562 --> 42:12.764
Uh, is there anything I can do?

42:18.203 --> 42:19.738
Hello?

42:21.039 --> 42:22.708
<i>I need to see you.</i>

42:24.142 --> 42:25.911
<i>Can you do that for me?</i>

42:32.383 --> 42:34.620
Yeah. Yeah, I can do that.

43:01.079 --> 43:02.814
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

43:03.081 --> 43:05.083
<i>***</i>

43:40.118 --> 43:43.054
